<item>
            <title>[SOLR-12214] Leader may skip publish itself as ACTIVE even its last published state is DOWN</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12214</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Found this problem on beasting LeaderVoteWaitTimeout,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a replica publish itself as DOWN on RecoveryStrategy.pingLeader()&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It won the election (by vote wait timeout) then skipping publish itself as ACTIVE (by looking into clusterstate, its state&#160;still ACTIVE).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ends up with a&#160;leader with DOWN state!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Therefore, replica should look into both clusterstate and its local last published state on skipping publish itself as ACTIVE&lt;/p&gt;</description>
